    summary: "Burton Malkiel argues that stock prices follow a random walk and that consistently beating the market is nearly impossible. He examines fundamental analysis, technical analysis, and modern portfolio theory, concluding that low-cost index funds are the best investment for most people. The book debunks popular investment myths while providing practical advice for building a diversified portfolio across different life stages.",
